Description:
City and water views!
CONTACT US TODAY FOR YOUR OWN PRIVATE VIEWING
One step inside this stunning 2 bedroom, 2 bathroom apartment and prepare to be overwhelmed by the sense of space, depth and breathtaking views on show.
Superbly set metres from Chapel Street, discover a stone-topped Miele kitchen with entertainers island bench, flowing through to open-plan living/dining.
The seamless floorplan flows outside to a fabulous, full-width balcony boasting sweeping views of the striking city skyline and the blue waters of the bay.
* 2 large bedrooms with mirrored BIR, main with fully tiled ensuite
* Luxurious, fully tiled bathroom with timber-framed vanity and mirrored cabinetry
* Concealed laundry
* Ducted heating and cooling
* Handy study nook
* Basement parking
* Roller blinds over openable windows
So close to city-bound trains and trams, enjoy a residents rooftop retreat with breathtaking 360 degree views, fully equipped gym and an inviting pool.
For more information, please contact Andrew McCalman today.

Description:
Inspired style, idyllic lifestyle
Serene, stylish and sophisticated, this distinctive residence has been completely transformed by a new designer renovation. Delivering exceptional inner urban lifestyle in a coveted location, walking distance to Melbourne's botanical precinct and Fawkner Park, this home showcases stunning designer style. Welcomed by a landscaped outdoor entertaining area boasting natural stone paving and lush green canopy, expanses of glass creates a seamless connection to the curated interiors. Natural oak timber floors flow through light filled open plan living and dining and a superb kitchen appointed with a suite of Miele appliances and ample storage, set against natural stone benchtops and splashback. On the first floor, the master bedroom with generously appointed walk in robe and ensuite is complemented by a second bedroom with built in robes and ensuite. This residence includes private security access, two secure undercover parking spaces, reverse cycle heating and cooling, communal tennis court, separate powder room and laundry.

Description:
Panoramic Views, Spectacular Renovation
Showcasing spectacular panoramic views across Melbourne spanning the majestic Macedon and Dandenong Ranges to the heart of our sports and entertainment precinct and city skyline, this stunning residence situated on the eleventh floor of the prestigious Lonsdale complex at Como with two secure carparks and storage epitomises contemporary living. A brand-new renovation boasts exacting attention to detail with premium finishes including custom cabinetry, timber flooring, Bose speakers and ducted heating and cooling. Comprising of an inviting, sizeable entrance foyer, a gourmet kitchen with double Neff ovens and microwave, integrated ASKO dishwasher, integrated double Liebherr fridge/freezer, five burner Ilve gas stovetop, stone benchtops and abundant storage, a versatile north facing, open plan living and dining domain with floor to ceiling glass to an undercover entertainers balcony plus a palatial bathroom with laundry facilities. Two generous bedrooms (BIRs) share a second balcony with the master suite also featuring a dressing room and luxurious ensuite with an oversized shower and twin basins. The exclusive community has access to an indoor pool, gym, spa, sauna, lift and an onsite caretaker. Como Green, the Vogue shopping centre and Palace Cinema are all easily accessed from the apartment whilst South Yarra Station, trams, an array of dining options and boutique shops on Toorak Road and Chapel Street offer a dress circle lifestyle like no other.
In conjunction with Valda Walsh of Walsh Cairnes & Co P/L

Description:
PRIVATE NEGOTIATION
OBVIOUS
This Victorian terrace, built in 1895, is a timeless beauty that youll want to wake up with. It has all the period details youd expect: ceiling roses, hallway arches and leadlight features throughout. The main bedroom with gas fireplace, timber shutters and glass double doors opening to the secure front courtyard is the ideal spot to linger over morning coffee. A second bedroom has double doors, which open to the cobblestone pathway. While the north-facing open plan kitchen and living area benefit from abundant natural light, served up through skylights and windows overlooking a peaceful garden. Additional features include heating, cooling and a large dual-access bathroom and laundry. The home is securely located behind a rendered fence and has extra entry points via the front lock-up garage and rear lane, too. Get the benefit of a quiet leafy street, plus the nearby perks of Fawkner Park, the Botanic Gardens, Toorak Road and Chapel Street.
SEALS THE DEAL
Historic character and the chance to put your own present-day spin on it.

Description:
Generously Proportioned with Panoramic Views
Designed and constructed in an era when quality and abundant size with room to move were paramount, this house-like apartment is (approximately 99 sqm in total size) takes pride of place within a tightly held boutique complex on the eighth floor, soaking in impressive panoramic views. Fully refurbished, the substantial interiors bask in natural light and benefit from a fresh coat of white paint throughout. An entrance lobby with in-built storage leads to a sun-filled lounge room with floor to ceiling windows opening to the balcony with a stunning backdrop of leafy tree tops and district views, a designated dining area which flows to the large separate kitchen with copious cupboard space and dishwasher. Two zoned and spacious bedrooms with built in robes and a further third bedroom off the lounge room boast views towards the city skyline. The expansive bathroom with separate bath and washing machine facilities, powder room, heating/cooling, lift access direct to the apartment and undercover off street parking provide the upmost comfort. With trams on the doorstep, Toorak Village, Chapel Street and Rockley Gardens all within easy reach, this downsizer dream ticks all the boxes.

Designed by Rob Mills architects and crowned by the gardens of Paul Bangay this brand new residence benefits from a north western orientation, bathed in natural light which is complimented by the 3.3m ceilings throughout. Offering 3 bedrooms, all with dedicated en-suite bathrooms and the main bedroom featuring a palatial dressing room and walk in robe, stunning entertainers kitchen with scullery that over looks the informal family and dining area (gas OFP) then seamlessly connecting to the outdoor garden terrace. A second living zone is perfectly set for formal sitting room (gas OFP) and also benefits from a connected custom study. Features: dual lift access, triple private garaging, extensive storage, separate powder room, laundry, heating and cooling throughout.
A commitment to craftsmanship without compromise from Pask Group; from the monumental isernia limestone façade, exquisite finishes including Italian Calcutta marble and Royal Oak floors, all elements have been carefully considered to bring together a unique offering in arguably Melbourne's most prestigious and sought-after location.
Insights: 49 other 3 bedroom unit in South Yarra have recently been sold.

Description:
A Prime Lifestyle Location for the First Home Buyer
Designed and constructed with a clear emphasis on space, quality and maximising natural light, this solid first floor apartment with off street parking positioned at the rear of a boutique building enjoys a coveted setting amongst tree-lined Rockley Road. Mere footsteps from Rockley Gardens, trams, the enticing Tivoli Bakery, cafés, restaurants, wine bars and shopping plus South Yarra Station and the Yarra River are an easy stroll away. Pristine interiors reflect the care with which this apartment has been preserved whilst contemporary updates such as a recently renovated bathroom, washing machine facilities, split system heating/cooling, Rinnai wall furnace, timber floorboards and carpeted bedrooms add to the comfort. The floorplan boasts a neatly presented kitchen/meals with dishwasher and gas cooking, a bright lounge room with floor to ceiling glass bestowing a leafy outlook which opens to the balcony, two sizeable sun-filled bedrooms with built in robes, a refurbished bathroom with bath as well as a shower and a separate toilet.
